summary: CNN political commentator Alice Stewart has passed away at the age of 58. Stewart was a veteran GOP advisor and journalist who appeared on various news networks, including CNN, MSNBC, and Fox News. She had a long and successful career in politics and journalism, and her insights will be missed by viewers and colleagues alike.

name: Dallas Stars
summary: The Dallas Stars have advanced to the second round of the 2024 Stanley Cup Playoffs after eliminating the Colorado Avalanche in a hard-fought six-game series. The Stars won the deciding Game 6 in double overtime, with Matt Duchene scoring the series-clinching goal. The Stars had previously won Games 3 and 4 in Colorado, while the Avalanche took Games 1, 2, and 5. The Stars will now face a yet-to-be-determined opponent in the second round. The Avalanche, who won the President's Trophy this season with the NHL's best regular-season record, were eliminated for the second consecutive year in the first round.

name: Las Vegas Aces
summary: The Las Vegas Aces are under investigation by the WNBA over a $100,000 annual sponsorship deal with the city's tourism authority for each player on the roster. This sponsorship, which is unprecedented in league history, has drawn attention and raised concerns about potential conflicts of interest. Despite the investigation, the Aces have celebrated their second championship with a banner ceremony and ring presentation, while also adding former Iowa basketball star Kate Martin to their roster. The details of the sponsorship are still under scrutiny, but it has generated significant discussion within the league and the sports world at large.

name: Scottie Scheffler news
summary: Scottie Scheffler, a renowned golfer, was arrested outside the PGA Championship in Louisville. Despite the arrest, he returned to the tournament and played the second round. Initial reports indicated that there was no body camera footage of the incident, and the Louisville mayor commented on the situation. The nature of Scheffler's arrest has drawn attention, with ESPN and CNN reporting that he was arrested for assaulting a police officer. Scheffler has since released a statement, and PGA TOUR confirmed his participation in the second round. CBS Sports noted that Scheffler's arrest ended his 41-round par-or-better streak, while NBC DFW reported on his performance in the second round. Yahoo Sports provided details about Scheffler warming up in a jail cell before the round, where he managed to shoot a five-under 67. The incident has also sparked reactions from PGA Championship fans, as reported by WAVE 3, highlighting the impact of the arrest both on the tournament and the wider public.
